RadVision Advances Most in a Week, Paring Gap With U.S. Shares

-- B y   G w e n   A c k e r m a n
-- 
2011-10-06T11:31:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-06/radvision-advances-most-in-a-week-paring-gap-with-u-s-shares.html
RadVision Ltd. (RVSN)  jumped the most in a
week in  Tel Aviv  trading, trimming the gap with U.S.-traded
shares.  The stock advanced 5 percent to 19.65 shekels, or the
equivalent of $5.28, as of 1:12 p.m. in Tel Aviv, after slumping
9.6 percent yesterday. The shares closed down 4.8 percent at
$5.31 in New York yesterday after the maker of video-
conferencing systems cut its third-quarter earnings forecast.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gwen Ackerman in Jerusalem at 
 gackerman@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  